he procedure.Â Please remove any metallic objects from area of scan. If sedation is required notify the CT department prior to procedure. Patient should be dressed in hospital gown only. Intact hospital and applicable allergy ID bands required. Patient restrictions include: no phosphodiesterase (ie. Viagra, Cialis, Levitra) or barium studies 48 hours prior, no smoking, no caffeine (coffee,tea,cola), no alcohol 12 hours prior.;Outpatient Clinical Communication: Patient to follow nutrition requirements, no solid food 4 hours prior to exam, clear fluids (no caffeine) and regular medications are allowed. 12 hours prior, no smoking, no caffeine (coffee,tea,cola), no alcohol. No Phosphodiesterase (ie. Viagra, Cialis, Levitra) or Barium studies 48 hours prior. No exercise on day of exam. Patient to bring eye glasses and hearing aids to the DI department. Please remove any metallic objects from area of scan. Hospital and applicable allergy ID bands required and provided at time of registration. Patient will be required to change into hospital gown upon arrival. Notify the CT department if Translation Service is required prior to the procedure. Patient restrictions include: no phosphodiesterase (ie. Viagra, Cialis, Levitra) or barium studies 48 hours prior, no smoking, no caffeine (coffee,tea,cola), no alcohol 12 hours prior.;</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Synonyms</key><value>CT Cardiac ScoreCT Coronary Nonenhanced Scoring</value></item></items></annotations><definition xsi:type="INSTRUCTION" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1" concept_name="Service request" max="1" name="CT Coronary Calcium Score"/><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">B48161A11EF4549FFAE82EE73B385AF5</digest></integrity_checks><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.service_request_information.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">230A8D964017